<DOC><DOCNO> AP890410-0136 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-10-89 2037EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Salvador     04-10 0229</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Salvador,0236</SECOND><HEAD>72 Guerrillas Killed In Fighting, Army Says</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leftist guerrillas attacked acivil defense post and a coffee processing plant west of SanSalvador Monday, an army spokesman said.   Seven civil patrolmen were seriously wounded and the militarypost was destroyed in the attacks near Comasagua, 17 miles from thecapital, civilian sources in the area said.   The army spokesman, who spoke on condition of anonymity,reported casualties but gave no details. He said the El Rosariocoffee processing plant suffered an undetermined amount of damage.   In fighting last week that ended Thursday, at least 100 peoplewere killed, the army and guerrillas said.   An army communique Monday said government troops killed 72rebels and wounded 103 others. It said the rebels killed 17civilians, wounded 23 and kidnapped 10 others.   The rebels, in a broadcast over their clandestine RadioVenceremos, said they killed or wounded 438 soldiers during theperiod, 255 of them in an attack on the 4th Infantry Brigade in thenorthern province of Chalatenango on Thursday. At the time, thearmy said three soldiers were killed and five others wounded.   The army said it confiscated mines, other explosives and 30rifles from the guerrillas. Rebels said they took army rifles andradios.   About 70,000 people, the majority of them civilians, have beenkilled in the 9-year-old war.</TEXT></DOC>